{"LOT":[{"def":"That which happens without human design or forethought; chance; accident; hazard; fortune; fate.","pos":""},{"def":"Anything (as a die, pebble, ball, or slip of paper) used in determining a question by chance, or without man's choice or will; as, to cast or draw lots.","pos":""}],"LOTE":[{"def":"A large tree (Celtis australis), found in the south of Europe.","pos":""}],"LOTHARIO":[{"def":"A gay seducer of women; a libertine.","pos":""}],"LOTION":[{"def":"A washing, especially of the skin for the purpose of rendering it fair.","pos":""},{"def":"A liquid preparation for bathing the skin, or an injured or diseased part, either for a medicinal purpose, or for improving its appearance.","pos":""}],"LOTONG":[{"def":"An East Indian monkey (Semnopithecus femoralis).","pos":""}],"LOTOPHAGI":[{"def":"A people visited by Ulysses in his wanderings.","pos":""}],"LOTTERY":[{"def":"A scheme for the distribution of prizes by lot or chance; esp.","pos":""},{"def":"Allotment; thing allotted.","pos":""}],"LOTTO":[{"def":"A game of chance, played with cards, on which are inscribed numbers, and any contrivance (as a wheel containing numbered balls) for determining a set of numbers by chance.","pos":""}],"LOTUS":[{"def":"An ornament much used in Egyptian architecture, generally asserted to have been suggested by the Egyptian water lily.","pos":""},{"def":"One who ate the fruit or leaf of the lotus, and, as a consequence, gave himself up to indolence and daydreams; one of the Lotophagi.","pos":""}]}